# iOS bundle identifier — do not change

The production iOS app uses **`com.vyooo`**. It is live on the App Store and registered in Firebase (**vyooo (ios)**). This identifier must stay the same.

## Do not modify

- **`PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER`** in `ios/Runner.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj`: main **Runner** target must remain **`com.vyooo`**; **RunnerTests** should stay **`com.vyooo.RunnerTests`** (or equivalent under the same app id family).
- **`BUNDLE_ID`** in `ios/Runner/GoogleService-Info.plist` for this app.
- **`iosBundleId`** for iOS in `lib/firebase_options.dart`.

## Apple Developer team (signing)

**`com.vyooo`** is tied to exactly one Apple Developer **Team** (the one that created the App Store app). Do **not** hardcode a random `DEVELOPMENT_TEAM` in `project.pbxproj` for all developers: another team’s ID causes *“app identifier cannot be registered… not available”* because Apple will not assign the same bundle id to two teams.

Each machine should use **Xcode → Signing & Capabilities → Team** with an Apple ID that is a member of the team that **owns** `com.vyooo`. Osama’s iPhone must be registered under that same team (Devices + development profile).

## If device signing or “bundle id not available” errors appear

Do **not** change the bundle id. Fix **team + provisioning**:

- Sign in to Xcode with the Apple ID that has access to the **Metatech / Vyooo** developer team (or whoever owns the App Store app).
- Pick that **Team** for the Runner target; enable **Automatically manage signing**.
- Ensure the device is added to the team’s devices if profiles are manual.

Using a different bundle id would create a **separate** app (new App Store listing / new Firebase iOS app), which is not acceptable for this product.
